HDFS
1.Hadoop distributed file system(hdfs) provide storage and access to data across hadoop in order to process the data.
2.It is a scalable fault-tolerant storage at low cost.
3.It detects and compensates for harware issue including disk problem and server failure.
4.store file across the collection of cluster.
5.In hdfs files are divided in the blocks of default value 128 mb.
6.Also provide replication having default value of 3 in each machine.
